usdPppoeProfileMIB.name: usdPppoeProfileMIB

revisions.description: Added PADI flag and packet trace support.
Added duplicate MAC address indicator and AC-NAME tag objects.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdPppoeProfileMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPppoeProfileMIB.description: The point-to-point protocol over Ethernet (PPPoE) profile MIB for the Juniper enterprise.

usdPppoeProfileTable.name: usdPppoeProfileTable
usdPppoeProfileTable.description: This table contains profiles for configuring PPPoE interfaces/sessions. Entries in this table are created/deleted as a side-effect of corresponding operations to the usdProfileNameTable in the Unisphere-Data-PROFILE-MIB.

usdPppoeProfileEntry.name: usdPppoeProfileEntry
usdPppoeProfileEntry.description: A profile describing configuration of a PPPoE interface and its subinterfaces (sessions).

usdPppoeProfileId.name: usdPppoeProfileId
usdPppoeProfileId.description: The integer identifier associated with this profile. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating a profile name in the usdProfileNameTable.

usdPppoeProfileSetMap.name: usdPppoeProfileSetMap
usdPppoeProfileSetMap.description: A bitmap representing which objects in this entry have been explicitly configured. See the definition of the UsdSetMap TEXTUAL-CONVENTION for details of use. The INDEX object(s) and this object are excluded from representation (i.e. their bits are never set). When a SET request does not explicitly configure UsdSetMap, bits in UsdSetMap are set as a side-effect of configuring other profile attributes in the same entry. If, however, a SET request explicitly configures UsdSetMap, the explicitly configured value overrides 1) any previous bit settings, and 2) any simultaneous 'side-effect' settings that would otherwise occur. Once set, bits can only be cleared by explicitly configuring UsdSetMap.

usdPppoeProfileMaxNumSessions.name: usdPppoeProfileMaxNumSessions
usdPppoeProfileMaxNumSessions.description: The maximum number of PPPoE sessions (subinterfaces) that can be configured on the main PPPoE interface created using this profile. A value of zero indicates no bound is configured.

usdPppoeProfileSubMotm.name: usdPppoeProfileSubMotm
usdPppoeProfileSubMotm.description: A message to send via a PADM on the sub-interface when this profile is applied to the IP interface above this PPPoE sub- interface. A client may choose to display this message to the user.

usdPppoeProfileSubUrl.name: usdPppoeProfileSubUrl
usdPppoeProfileSubUrl.description: A URL to be sent via a PADM on the sub-interface when this profile is applied to the IP interface above this PPPoE sub-interface. The string entered here can have several substitutions applied: %D is replaced with the profile name %d is replaced with the domain name %u is replaced with the user name %U is replaced with the user/domain name together %% is replaced with the % character The resulting string must not be greater than 127 octets long. The client may use this URL as the initial web-page for the user.

usdPppoeProfileDupProtect.name: usdPppoeProfileDupProtect
usdPppoeProfileDupProtect.description: Flag to control whether duplicate MAC addresses are allowed

usdPppoeProfileAcName.name: usdPppoeProfileAcName
usdPppoeProfileAcName.description: The name to use for the AC-NAME tag that is sent in any PADO that is sent on this interface.

usdPppoeProfilePadiFlag.name: usdPppoeProfilePadiFlag
usdPppoeProfilePadiFlag.description: The PPPoE major interface parameter PADI flag controls whether to always repsond to a PADI with a PADO regardless of the ability to create the session and allow the session establish phase to resolve it.

usdPppoeProfilePacketTrace.name: usdPppoeProfilePacketTrace
usdPppoeProfilePacketTrace.description: The PPPoE major interface parameter packet tracing flag controls whether packet tracing is enable or not.

usdPppoeProfileCompliance.name: usdPppoeProfileCompliance
usdPppoeProfileCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper PPPoE Profile MIB. This statement became obsolete when the duplicate MAC address indicator and AC-NAME tag were added.

usdPppoeCompliance2.name: usdPppoeCompliance2
usdPppoeCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper PPPoE profile MIB. This statement became obsolete when PADI flag, AC-name and packet trace objects were added.

usdPppoeCompliance3.name: usdPppoeCompliance3
usdPppoeCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper PPPoE Profile MIB.

usdPppoeProfileGroup.name: usdPppoeProfileGroup
usdPppoeProfileGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPPoE interfaces in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when the duplicate MAC address indicator and AC-NAME tag objects were added.

usdPppoeProfileGroup2.name: usdPppoeProfileGroup2
usdPppoeProfileGroup2.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPPOE interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when PADI flag, AC-name and packet trace objects were added.

usdPppoeProfileGroup3.name: usdPppoeProfileGroup3
usdPppoeProfileGroup3.description: A collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPPOE interfaces in a Unisphere product.
